    "body": "@l33ds With regard to you not seeing the error \"bind failed: Address already in use\", we do indicate  indicate non success by returning 0 from bind(), and the error message should be in the logs. What might have happened in your observation of the clients connecting \"successfully\" to the server is that the clients didn't error out, but were left in a reconnection loop.\r\n\r\nFor example, if you have an invalid certificate, the client will continue attempting to connect forever, and forever failing with the ssl mismatch error."
